              <span id="reviewTextContainer2198032952" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17503021835062108139"><i>The Broken Girls</i> was an absolute delight, <b>exceeding all of my expectations</b>. This story will definitely stick with me!<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1548434355ra/26969902.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I went into this with very little knowledge of the plot. The only information I had was that it was a Mystery set at an all-girls Prep School in Vermont.<br/><br/>While I intensely love this set-up, upon reading, I pleasantly discovered there is a lot more to this story than that brief description lets on. <br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1478231019ra/21049765.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This novel is replete with an absorbing <b>gothic atmosphere</b> that transports you in time</span>
  <span id="freeText17503021835062108139" style="display:none"><i>The Broken Girls</i> was an absolute delight, <b>exceeding all of my expectations</b>. This story will definitely stick with me!<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1548434355ra/26969902.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I went into this with very little knowledge of the plot. The only information I had was that it was a Mystery set at an all-girls Prep School in Vermont.<br><br>While I intensely love this set-up, upon reading, I pleasantly discovered there is a lot more to this story than that brief description lets on. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1478231019ra/21049765.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This novel is replete with an absorbing <b>gothic atmosphere</b> that transports you in time and place. <br><br>It is the perfect amount of suspense, with <b>extra special paranormal goodness sprinkled on top!</b><br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1545058662ra/26760552.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>The main portion of the story alternates back and forth between 1950 and 2014. The narrative follows different women in and around Barrens, Vermont, and more importantly <i>Idlewilde Hall</i>. <br><br>I certainly wish I hadn't put off reading this for months after getting it. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1588495388ra/29402409.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I can't explain it. It just kept getting shuffled down the ole' TBR list. <br><br>Now, I can say, <b>I am physically distraught at not having picked this up as soon as I received it.</b> <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1545058662ra/26760553.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Admittedly, that may be taking it a little far, I am nothing if not dramatic, but I do wish I would have picked it up immediately. <br><br>Honestly, I do not have even one constructive criticism for this story.<br><br>This book is incredible. This book wants you to read it. This book will keep you up nights. READ IT!<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1498143091ra/23099170.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Thank you so much to the publisher, Berkley Publishing Group, for providing me with a copy to read and review. <br><br>I apologize to you ((and myself)) that I didn't get to it until now!</span>
