<div id="review_2942801331" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2942801331" />
    <a title="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill"><img alt="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1584753242p2/72904050.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2942801331?book_show_action=true">May 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill" href="/user/show/72904050-kim-it-s-all-about-the-thrill">Kim ~ It’s All About the Thrill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2942801331" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18378937896555425316"><br/>3.5 stars<br/>You say this is a book about a super creepy all girls boarding school? You say there are ghosts? You say that the vibe is super goth? I say yessss please! Hand it over, give it to me now. Okay this book has to have been the most recommended book to me ever since I have been on Goodreads. Probably because The Sun Down Motel is one of my favorite thrillers ever. Yep it is on my little Goodreads shelf of all time favorites. Yet...this one didn&apos;t do it for me like Sun Down did.<br/><br/>You have a de</span>
  <span id="freeText18378937896555425316" style="display:none"><br />3.5 stars<br />You say this is a book about a super creepy all girls boarding school? You say there are ghosts? You say that the vibe is super goth? I say yessss please! Hand it over, give it to me now. Okay this book has to have been the most recommended book to me ever since I have been on Goodreads. Probably because The Sun Down Motel is one of my favorite thrillers ever. Yep it is on my little Goodreads shelf of all time favorites. Yet...this one didn't do it for me like Sun Down did.<br /><br />You have a deserted boarding school with a crazy history. Nobody wants to touch this property with a ten foot pole. It sits there locked up behind the iron gates. With a history of ghosts, deaths and girls that are "broken." Yet along comes an investor and wants to reopen this creepy place. Who on earth would send their daughter there? That is a question Fiona wants answered. She can't move on from the wicked history. Especially since her own sister was found murdered on the grounds many years ago. <br /><br />This book has some stellar reviews and it is very popular! This may just be a "it is a me thing." Why, I am not sure but it just didn't grab me like her other book did. When I read Sun Down I felt I was there at the motel, that place was creepy! I felt every fiber of that story. This one I just didn't connect with any of the characters, I didn't find it all that creepy. The back story of Mary Hand just felt a little hard to believe. It just wasn't a page turner for me and I found my mind wandering. Again, probably a me thing...we can't love them all.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18378937896555425316" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


